---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="DonateCrate Neighborhood Rollout"
  description="See how DonateCrate launches neighborhood-by-neighborhood to keep pickup routes dense and reliable."
>
  <main class="simple-page">
    <span class="eyebrow">Neighborhood Rollout</span>
    <h1>We expand by route quality, not by claiming a whole city at once.</h1>
    <p class="simple-page__lede">
      DonateCrate launches in compact service pockets first so pickup windows stay reliable, route density stays high,
      and support remains local.
    </p>
    <div class="simple-grid">
      <article>
        <h2>Active Launch Area</h2>
        <p>Current rollout is centered on the Knoxville `37922` anchor zone with nearby eligible addresses.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h2>Pending Areas</h2>
        <p>Addresses near active routes may show as pending while we build enough density for a clean monthly cycle.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h2>Expansion Signal</h2>
        <p>Waitlist volume, route adjacency, and operational efficiency shape where we open next.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </main>
</SiteLayout>
